messages.message:
Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1

Thanks, Davido, for this change. Looking forward to see JSch removed :-)
Can we add one test for demonstrating that this change doesn't break anything?

Patch Set 2:

> Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1
> 
> Thanks, Davido, for this change. Looking forward to see JSch removed :-)
> Can we add one test for demonstrating that this change doesn't break anything?

The corresponding gerrit core change is running dozen (or hundreds?) of unit and intergrations tests using Apache MINA SSH client. Isn't this enough?

The real test would be:

* Set up gerrit site from the gerrit core change: [1]
* Set-up replication plugin
* Configure couple of destinations
* Confirm that the replication works as expected

[1] https://gerrit-review.googlesource.com/c/gerrit/+/269976

Patch Set 2:

> Patch Set 2:
> 
> > Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1
> > 
> > Thanks, Davido, for this change. Looking forward to see JSch removed :-)
> > Can we add one test for demonstrating that this change doesn't break anything?
> 
> The corresponding gerrit core change is running dozen (or hundreds?) of unit and intergrations tests using Apache MINA SSH client. Isn't this enough?
> 
> The real test would be:
> 
> * Set up gerrit site from the gerrit core change: [1]
> * Set-up replication plugin
> * Configure couple of destinations
> * Confirm that the replication works as expected
> 
> [1] https://gerrit-review.googlesource.com/c/gerrit/+/269976

^^^ Jacek did all this already and provided detailed description (Thanks for that!) in this comment: [1].

It's totally disappointing that we failed to deliver that great improvement in performance and stability of critical replication feature to gerrit users in 3.2 release ;-(

[1] https://bugs.chromium.org/p/gerrit/issues/detail?id=11688#c6

Patch Set 2:

> Patch Set 2:
> 
> > Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1
> > 
> > Thanks, Davido, for this change. Looking forward to see JSch removed :-)
> > Can we add one test for demonstrating that this change doesn't break anything?
> 
> The corresponding gerrit core change is running dozen (or hundreds?) of unit and intergrations tests using Apache MINA SSH client. Isn't this enough?

Apologies, I did not express myself clearly. I was asking for a test that the replication plugin works with this change.

> The real test would be:
> 
> * Set up gerrit site from the gerrit core change: [1]
> * Set-up replication plugin
> * Configure couple of destinations
> * Confirm that the replication works as expected

Yes, we do already the ReplicationIT suite that simulates this by using the same Gerrit server as source and destination and that works. I am wondering if we can extend that suite.

Hope this clarifies.
